j.collections

Class ArrayQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • j.collections.ArrayQueue<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Class of the element.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Queue<E>

    public class ArrayQueue<E>
extends java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
implements java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Queue<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.io.Serializable
    A FIFO queue implemented using a circular array that dynamically resizes when out of space. This queue implementation permits null elements. This class is not thread-safe.
